sec.p:
Regarding age (
Figure 3
), respiratory symptoms showed a decreased risk with age (panel A, log rank p-value for trend = 0.007) while an overall increased risk with age was observed for neurological & cognitive dysfunction and fatigue (panel B and C respectively, p<0.005 for both), while and no differences among age classes were found for gastrointestinal symptoms (panel D, p=0.90).
